We have encountered an issue getting our Limelight values from our network table. Using the LimelightHelpers, we get null values but also directly accessing the network table with the name matching hostname (limelight-tags) only returns 0.0 (which we set as default value). Is there a way to get a list of all network tables, or to solve our current issue via other means? Down below is some code from the limelight website.

LimelightHelpers.SetRobotOrientation(“limelight-tags”, m_poseEstimator.getEstimatedPosition().getRotation().getDegrees(), 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
LimelightHelpers.PoseEstimate mt2 = LimelightHelpers.getBotPoseEstimate_wpiBlue_MegaTag2(“limelight-tags”);
if(Math.abs(m_gyro.getRate()) > 720) // if our angular velocity is greater than 720 degrees per second, ignore vision updates
{
doRejectUpdate = true;
}
if(mt2.tagCount == 0)
{
doRejectUpdate = true;
}
if(!doRejectUpdate)
{
m_poseEstimator.setVisionMeasurementStdDevs(VecBuilder.fill(.7,.7,9999999));
m_poseEstimator.addVisionMeasurement(
mt2.pose,
mt2.timestampSeconds);
}

Thanks in advance for the help!
